{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a managed office space?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A managed office is a fully furnished, ready-to-use workspace where the provider handles everything — furniture, internet, electricity, housekeeping, security, reception and maintenance. You just walk in and start working. Unlike coworking (shared desks), managed offices give you a dedicated, private space for your team."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is a managed office different from coworking?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Coworking offers shared desks in an open space with other companies. Managed offices give you a private, dedicated area exclusively for your team — with your own branding, layout, and access control. Managed offices are better for enterprises needing privacy, security, and custom configurations."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the typical lock-in period for a managed office?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most providers offer 11-month to 3-year agreements. WorkEZ offers flexible terms starting from 11 months, with options to scale up or down based on your team size."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I customize the office layout in a managed office?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Enterprise clients can customize their workspace with branded signage, custom furniture layouts, dedicated meeting rooms, server rooms, and specialized IT infrastructure. WorkEZ handles the entire fit-out process."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the advantages of a managed office over a traditional lease?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Key advantages: zero CAPEX (no fit-out cost), flexible terms (vs 3-9 year leases), all-inclusive pricing (internet, power, housekeeping included), faster setup (days vs months), and the ability to scale up or down without penalty."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How quickly can I move into a managed office?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Standard configurations are ready within 48 hours to 2 weeks. Custom enterprise fit-outs typically take 4-8 weeks depending on complexity."}}]}


